      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>Marmite stock </strong>and <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened and the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>beef & carrot</strong> <strong>hotpot mix</strong></p>",
